 lot here at Not Boring. It&#8217;s personal for us &#8212; it runs in our =
family. So any time it comes up in the news, it naturally catches my eye. T=
he story above is less about any one specific breakthrough, but how the com=
bination of advancements made in early-detection and early-treatment is imp=
acting Alzheimer&#8217;s treatment. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Previously, we&#8=
